{"tid":303490,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"德國國會通過同性婚姻合法化議案","createTime":"2017-06-30T08:28:02.000Z","updateTime":"2017-06-30T10:49:50.000Z","uid":41404,"like":13,"dislike":6,"uniUserReply":0,"replies":[{"pid":"d59b3b9633a98d61e5b0bce9238603aa8b9320cd","tid":303490,"uid":41404,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T08:28:02.000Z","msg":"Germany's Bundestag passes bill on same-sex marriage<br />\nHomosexual couples in Germany will now be able to marry and adopt children under a new law passed by parliament. The move brings Germany into line with several other European countries.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://m.dw.com/en/germanys-bundestag-passes-bill-on-same-sex-marriage/a-39483785\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fm.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgermanys-bundestag-passes-bill-on-same-sex-marriage%2Fa-39483785&d=yPbTbF%2BwQaTv4I4YfP4w1i7PofNJLCAwyGXsi6MH%2FEQ%3D&h=ed9e0ad8\" target=\"_blank\">http://m.dw.com/en/germanys-bundestag-passes-bill-on-same-sex-marriage/a-39483785</a>"},{"pid":"d8b7ae6ace259b706a86a42359605ca4c4ee0e0b","tid":303490,"uid":60545,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T08:31:29.000Z","msg":"歐洲主要國家都齊"},{"pid":"42c44e6caca613201fca136aeaddebdf91566cb4","tid":303490,"uid":41404,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T09:13:09.000Z","msg":"The bill passed by 393 to 226, with four abstentions. Merkel herself voted against the bill, although her comments helped bring it about.<br />\n <br />\nHowever, more than 70 members of Merkel's conservative bloc must have voted in favor of the bill for it to pass.<br />\nMerkel later explained her &quot;no&quot; vote by saying that she understood the definition of marriage in the German constitution as referring solely to unions between men and women. She said, however, that she hoped the vote to approve gay marriage would lead to &quot;more social peace.&quot;<br />\nAlthough she voted against homosexual marriage, she said that after long reflection, she had come to the conclusion that same-sex couples should be able to adopt children, which is something the new bill will legalize.<br />\nVolker Beck of the Green party, who has long advocated legalizing same-sex marriage, called the vote &quot;a success for democracy,&quot; citing opinion polls showing that 80 percent of Germans were in favor of allowing homosexual couples to marry and adopt children."},{"pid":"f131466122b7067ea87c42ab37543e2b43757120","tid":303490,"uid":41404,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T09:19:22.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/media/DDjeFCmXkAAETfG?format=jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fpbs.twimg.com%2Fmedia%2FDDjeFCmXkAAETfG%3Fformat%3Djpg&h=6314e884&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\nGermanForeignOffice @GermanyDiplo<br />\n<br />\nThe German Parliament approved same-sex marriage. Congratulations to all gay couples who have been waiting to get married!"},{"pid":"8f5f7590b4b729fb945995dabca21145199665e4","tid":303490,"uid":41245,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T09:22:09.000Z","msg":"乜未㗎？<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n仲以為全世界得香港落後人地20年"},{"pid":"14cb9f7d8568d0c5f99e7f72c6349cc900cd6436","tid":303490,"uid":40216,"like":2,"dislike":5,"score":-3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-30T09:33:09.000Z","msg":"傳統德國價值已死<br />\nDie traditionelle Familie stirbt aus <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<img src=\"http://germanhistorydocs.ghi-dc.org/images/highres_00008437%20copy.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgermanhistorydocs.ghi-dc.org%2Fimages%2Fhighres_00008437%2520copy.jpg&h=597afef7&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<img src=\"https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/736x/00/3d/29/003d290757b702e